☕ Java Methods and Constructors Practice Questions (10–20)
🟢 Methods Practice Questions
1. Write a method add(int a, int b) that returns the sum of two numbers.
2. Write a method findMax(int a, int b) that returns the larger number.
3. Write a method isEven(int n) that returns true if the number is even, otherwise false.
4. Write a method factorial(int n) that returns the factorial of a number.
5. Write a method isPrime(int n) that checks whether a number is prime.
6. Write a method sumOfDigits(int n) that returns the sum of all digits of a number.
7. Write a method reverseNumber(int n) that returns the reverse of a number.
8. Write a method calculateArea(double radius) that returns the area of a circle.
9. Write a method printTable(int n) that prints the multiplication table of a number.
10. Write a method findLargest(int a, int b, int c) that returns the largest among three numbers.
